# Planner Engine Guide (Start to End)

This file explains how the planner system works, in plain language, from the moment a user opens Planner to the moment tasks are committed.

It also includes a comparison:
- what users can actually do in the current UI
- what exists in engine/code but is not fully used or not visible in UI yet

If you want to safely modify behavior, read this file first, then edit one layer at a time (UI, actions, engine, or DB mapping).

---

## 1) Big Picture: What the planner does

The planner turns your study structure into a date-based schedule.

At a high level, it does this:
1. Collects your structure (subjects, chapters/topics, tasks, durations, dates, dependencies).
2. Collects your constraints (start date, deadline, daily capacity, off-days, etc.).
3. Converts that data into "units" for the engine.
4. Runs feasibility checks (can this fit?) and scheduling (where does each session go?).
5. Shows preview so you can edit manually.
6. Optionally re-optimizes around pinned/manual items.
7. Commits final plan to tasks + snapshot history.

