## 8) Real scheduling rules currently in force

If you change behavior, these are the rules users currently feel:

1. Topics are effectively processed in queue order per subject.
2. Dependencies block start until prerequisite topic is completed.
3. Deadlines and earliest_start are hard constraints.
4. Off-days remove days completely.
5. Capacity limits are enforced (with optional flex overflow).
6. Some advanced priority/order knobs are present but not strongly active.

